@x0b DELETE for [DriveItemVersion](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/onedrive/developer/rest-api/resources/driveitemversion?view=odsp-graph-online) probably didn't work for you, because documentation provides wrong path. Correct one is: `/drives/{drive-id}/items/{item-id}/versions/{version-id}`

I wrote simple script which uses rclone, curl and jq to clean up all old versions:
[onedrive-cleanup.sh](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/files/4838990/onedrive-cleanup.txt)

@Dibbyo456 Thanks for pinging. I think this is great since we finally can control the versioning. Would you like to take on this and open a PR?

But speaking of multiple versions created by rclone, IIRC rclone doesn't set the modtime afterwards now as @ncw described (except for [one trivial point](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/issues/2520#issuecomment-418427375)), so the extra versions _should_ only come from overwriting existing files... But things might have changed over time, so some more checking would be good. @Zvezdin Are you seeing multiple versions even for new files, or just for overwritten files?

Apart from that, a `cleanup` command would be good to have anyway.
